  "text": "For the first step, we have to minimize the makespan when scheduling identical tasks on heterogeneous processors and without release dates. Without communication costs, this is a well-known load balancing problem, which can be solved by a greedy algorithm [CITATION_1] . The ''scheduling backwards\" phase of SLJF follows this greedy algorithm and thus solves this load balancing problem optimally.",
